name: Air Fryer Beefy Vegan Taquitos
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Air-fried meaty, cheesy, spicy, crunchy, vegan taquitos that are sure to please. Serve with guacamole and salsa if desired.
ingredients: 1 (12 ounce) package vegetarian ground beef crumbles (such as MorningStar Farms®), thawed
2  canned chipotle chilies in adobo sauce, minced
2 tablespoons adobo sauce from chipotle peppers
½ (8 ounce) tub vegan cream cheese (such as Toffutti®)
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat
Add onion and garlic and cook for 3 minutes
Add vegetarian beef crumbles, chipotle peppers, adobo sauce, cumin, and onion powder
Add cream cheese, nutritional yeast, and salt
Cook until cheese is melted and everything is evenly combined, about 2 minutes
Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Spoon a heaping tablespoon of mixture into the middle of each tortilla and roll up
Working in batches, place a single layer of taquitos in the air fryer basket, seam-side down
Spray the tops with cooking spray
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate
